<!--
VOICING PLAN (4108 — I Know That My Redeemer Lives, D major):
- All F notes: accid.ges="s"; all C notes: accid.ges="s" (D major key).
- Non-diatonic chords: C#° and G#° substituted with Em (smooth diatonic neighbor).
- Structural rhythm: The hymn's LH and RH mirror the long-note melody (half-whole notes)
  with internal arpeggiation to add movement within held harmonies.
- Phrase 1 (1-4): Light opening — 2-note RH, 3-note LH. A7 uses C#4 consistently.
- Phrase 2 (5-8): Growing — DΔ7 arpeggio in bar 5, Em7 in bar 7, wide A spacing in bar 8.
- Phrase 3 (9-12): Development — quartal D opening, A7 suspension, full descending line
  in bar 11 tracking melody G-F#-E-F#.
- Phrase 4 (13-16): Climax — RH reaches G5 in bar 13; bar 14 dotted-half sustains high;
  bar 16 full five-string D2-A2-D3-A3 pedal tonic.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bar 1→2: RH D5→A4→B4 (inner voice step) while LH rises D3→A2 (contrary motion across
  the wide spacing).
- Bar 7: Em7→D²: RH G4-B4-D5 → A4-D5-F#5 all stepwise. LH contrary: E3→D3.
- Bar 10: All four beats step-wise: melody D-F#-A-D tracks RH F#-G-A-D. Inner thirds.
- Bar 11: Four chords all beat-by-beat with RH B-A-G-F# parallel thirds, LH G-D-A-D
  voice-leading model.
- Bar 14: Long dotted half in both melody and harp staves — sustained resonance before
  final cadence. Common D tone held across bar 14.
- Bar 16: Whole note final — LH provides D2-A2-D3-A3 full range pedal resonance.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Bars 1-4: Light — 2-note RH, 3-note LH, establishing D major character.
- Bars 5-8: Building — 7th chord enrichment (DΔ7, Em7), wider LH spacing.
- Bars 9-12: Full — quartal RH color (bar 9), 4-note LH throughout, descending sequences.
- Bars 13-16: Majestic close — RH reaches up to G5 (bar 13), then wide sustained sonority
  resolves to D2-D5 full range final chord.
-->
